<p>JavaScript can change HTML attributes.</p>
<p>In this case JavaScript changes the src (source) attribute of an image.</p>

<button 
    onclick="document.getElementById('myImage')
        .src='http://www.w3schools.com/html/pic_bulbon.gif'">Turn on the light</button>

<img id="myImage" src="http://www.w3schools.com/html/pic_bulboff.gif" style="width:100px">

<button
    onclick="document.getElementById('myImage')
        .src='http://www.w3schools.com/html/pic_bulboff.gif'">Turn off the light</button>


        <!-- :::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::: -->
